 actual timer interrupt - this may well give <br />slightly different behaviour, especially for code that uses network stuff <br />(and select()), because we're now more likely to calculate the load <br />averages at just the moment when any network activity has taken place..<br /><br />So you shouldn't be worried unless you actually _feel_ that it's slower <br />(remove the "xload" stuff first, because otherwise it will unconsciously <br />make you assume the machine is slower ;-)<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
